modules.description: This module provides creation, modification, and querying operations for immutable sets of `Fpath.path` values, supporting functional set manipulation with union, intersection, ordered iteration, and safe element retrieval. It enables tasks like path collection analysis, membership checks, and transformation through mapping and filtering, working entirely with `Fpath.set` structures without interacting with the file system. Use cases include managing include/exclude path lists, combining directory hierarchies, and deduplicating file paths from sequences.

Supports operations for constructing, manipulating, and normalizing file system paths as abstract values, including segment decomposition, extension management, and platform-agnostic normalization. It operates on path representations using `Fpath.t`, alongside set and map abstractions for managing path collections. Designed for cross-platform path handling, relativizing paths, and maintaining consistent path invariants without direct file system interaction.
